    "sub_topic": "Traveling salesman problem",
    "message_1": "A traveling salesman needs to visit 5 cities for business meetings. If the distances between the cities are as follows:\n- City 1 to City 2: 10 km\n- City 1 to City 3: 15 km\n- City 1 to City 4: 12 km\n- City 1 to City 5: 20 km\n- City 2 to City 3: 8 km\n- City 2 to City 4: 25 km\n- City 2 to City 5: 18 km\n- City 3 to City 4: 14 km\n- City 3 to City 5: 28 km\n- City 4 to City 5: 16 km\n\nWhat is the shortest distance that the salesman can travel in order to visit all 5 cities exactly once?",
    "message_2": "To find the shortest distance, we need to find the shortest path that visits all cities exactly once. We can use the brute force method to find all possible routes and then choose the shortest one.\n\nThere are 4! (factorial) possible routes since the salesman can start from City 1 and then visit the other cities in any order. 4! = 4 × 3 × 2 × 1 = 24 possible routes.\n\nHere are all the possible routes and their distances:\n\n1. 1-2-3-4-5: 10 + 8 + 14 + 16 = 48 km\n2. 1-2-3-5-4: 10 + 8 + 28 + 16 = 62 km\n3. 1-2-4-3-5: 10 + 25 + 14 + 28 = 77 km\n4. 1-2-4-5-3: 10 + 25 + 16 + 28 = 79 km\n5. 1-2-5-3-4: 10 + 18 + 14 + 14 = 56 km\n6. 1-2-5-4-3: 10 + 18 + 16 + 14 = 58 km\n7. 1-3-2-4-5: 15 + 8 + 25 + 16 = 64 km\n8. 1-3-2-5-4: 15 + 8 + 18 + 16 = 57 km\n9. 1-3-4-2-5: 15 + 14 + 25 + 18 = 72 km\n10. 1-3-4-5-2: 15 + 14 + 16 + 18 = 63 km\n11. 1-3-5-2-4: 15 + 28 + 18 + 25 = 86 km\n12. 1-3-5-4-2: 15 + 28 + 16 + 25 = 84 km\n13. 1-4-2-3-5: 12 + 8 + 14 + 28 = 62 km\n14. 1-4-2-5-3: 12 + 8 + 18 + 28 = 66 km\n15. 1-4-3-2-5: 12 + 14 + 8 + 18 = 52 km\n16. 1-4-3-5-2: 12 + 14 + 28 + 18 = 72 km\n17. 1-4-5-2-3: 12 + 16 + 18 + 8 = 54 km\n18. 1-4-5-3-2: 12 + 16 + 28 + 8 = 64 km\n19. 1-5-2-3-4: 20 + 18 + 14 + 14 = 66 km\n20. 1-5-2-4-3: 20 + 18 + 25 + 14 = 77 km\n21. 1-5-3-2-4: 20 + 28 + 8 + 25 = 81 km\n22. 1-5-3-4-2: 20 + 28 + 14 + 25 = 87 km\n23. 1-5-4-2-3: 20 + 16 + 25 + 8 = 69 km\n24. 1-5-4-3-2: 20 + 16 + 14 + 8 = 58 km\n\nThe shortest distance is 48 km, and the route is 1-2-3-4-5."
